Package com.barchart.util.anno

barchart annotations

See:
          Description

Annotation Types Summary
BuilderFor means this class has transient existence and is used to help build another class
EventListener means that method has event listener semantics; for the specified class
Implements helps to show interface that method implements
Mutable means mutable, changing, live object, which can also be modified explicitly
NotMutable means immutable, final, non changing value object
NotThreadSafe means need synchronization in multi thread environment
NotYetImplemented means class or method that should not be used as yet
ProxyTo means this class is using fields from another class
SynchronizedBy means this field is synchronized(object) over this object
ThreadSafe means can be used w/o special synchronization efforts
Updatable means changing, live object, which can NOT be modified explicitly BUT can be updated implicitly by an authorized process
UsedOnce means that method is called once on object init/registration
